Target: The Building Environment ontology (OntoBuiltEnv) is an ontology developed for representing key information about properties (i.e. buildings as well as flats/apartments). It combines information about building usage, key construction characteristics, location and address, and estimated property value. More detailed geometric information can be retrieved from the associated OntoCityGml representation.

Comment: A built structure which is available for occupation or business purposes.
Label: Property

Comment: A self-contained suite of rooms which occupies part of a building.
Label: Flat

Comment: A built structure with ground, roof, and walls which stands more or less permanently in one place.
Label: Building

Comment: A relationship between a flat/apartment and its parent building it is contained within.
Label: is in

Comment: Unique identifier describing the property.
Label: has identifier

Comment: Location of property footprint centroid in WGS84 coordinates.
Label: has WGS84 coordinates

Comment: An area defined for administrative purposes, e.g. a county or local authority district.
Label: Administrative district

Comment: A relationship between an administrative district and its actual official name.
Label: label

Comment: A relationship between a property and its address.
Label: has address

Comment: A relationship between an address and an encompassing administrative district.
Label: has administrative district

Comment: A code of letters and digits denoting a particular (mostly granular) geographic area used to aid in the sorting of mail.
Label: Postal code

Comment: A relationship between an address and the respective postal code.
Label: has postal code

Comment: A relationship between a postal code and its actual code of letters and digits.
Label: label

Comment: A relationship between an address and the respective street name.
Label: has street

Comment: A relationship between an address and the respective street/house number.
Label: has street number

Comment: A relationship between an address and the respective unit number, incl. potential description of the unit (e.g. "Flat 1", "Apartment A").
Label: has unit name

Comment: Name of the building where the address is located.  Often used in countries like England, India and Japan.
Label: has building name

Comment: A relationship between an address and a presumed match of the address in another knowledge base.
Label: has presumed match

Comment: A relationship between a property and an encompassing administrative district.
Label: located in

Comment: A relationship between a building and its corresponding instance IRI in OntoCityGml.
Label: has OntoCityGML representation

Comment: A relationship between a property and its total floor area.
Label: has total floor area

Comment: A relationship between a building and its ground elevation.
Label: has ground elevation

Comment: A relationship between a property and its (estimated) property value.
Label: has market value

Comment: A relationship between a building and its total installed photovoltaics area.
Label: has installed PV area

Comment: A relationship between a building and its total roof area.
Label: has total roof area

Comment: A relationship between a building and its roof area suitable for photovoltaics installation.
Label: has roof area suitable for PV
has roof area suitable for PV

Comment: Key construction component of a property (i.e. wall, floor, roof, window).
Label: Construction component

Comment: A relationship between a property and one of its key construction components.
Label: has construction component

Comment: Key construction characteristics of the property's walls.
Label: Wall

Comment: Key construction characteristics of the property's roof.
Label: Roof

Comment: Key construction characteristics of the property's windows.
Label: Window

Comment: Key construction characteristics of the property's floor.
Label: Floor

Comment: A relationship between a property and its construction dates.
Label: has construction date

Comment: A relationship between a property and its overall energy efficiency rating (e.g. linear 'A to G' rating (where A is the most energy efficient and G is the least energy efficient))
Label: has energy rating

Comment: A relationship between a property and its total number of habitable rooms.
Label: has number of habitable rooms

Comment: The built form of the property.
Label: Built form

Comment: A relationship between a property and its built form.
Label: has built form

Comment: A property with a detached built form.
Label: Detached

Comment: A property with a semi-detached built form.
Label: Semi-Detached

Comment: A property with a terraced built form.
Label: Terraced

Comment: The general type of the property.
Label: Property type

Comment: A relationship between a property and its property type.
Label: has property type

Comment: A dwelling that serves as living quarters for one or more families, with one or more storeys.
Label: House

Comment: A small house with a single story.
Label: Bungalow

Comment: Typically offsite manufactured bungalow-style homes that are located within a private estate.
Label: ParkHome

Comment: A self-contained apartment (usually on two floors) in a larger building and with its own entrance from the outside.
Label: Maisonette

Comment: Description of the (intended) usage and/or function of a property. One property can have multiple usages. If multiple usages are assigned to one property, they have an usage share assigned to them (for single usage assignments this is assumed 1).
Label: Property usage

Comment: A relationship between a property and its (intended) usage and/or function.
Label: has property usage

Comment: A relationship between a property usage and its relative share if property has multiple usages associated with it (between 0 and 1).
Label: usage share

Comment: A relationship between a property usage and a textual description of it (e.g. its name or (intended) usage classification).
Label: usage label

Comment: A relationship between a property and its latest Energy Performance record (i.e. unique lodgement identifier).
Label: latest EPC

Comment: A property that serves as living space for one or more parties.
Label: Domestic

Comment: A property that serves non-living purposes (i.e. commercial, industrial, public propertys).
Label: Non-Domestic

Comment: A property that serves as living space for one party.
Label: Single residential

Comment: A property that serves as living space for more than one party.
Label: Multi residential

Comment: Emergency services are organizations which ensure public safety and health by addressing different emergencies.
Label: Emergency service

Comment: Medical care includes sites which focus on the provision of secondary medical care services.
Label: Medical care

Comment: Education includes a very broad group of sites with a common high level primary function of providing education (either state funded or by fees).
Label: Education

Comment: A place of business where professional or clerical duties are performed.
Label: Office

Comment: A feature that sells to the general public finished goods.
Label: Retail establishment

Comment: A place where members of a religious group congregate for worship.
Label: Religious facility

Comment: A property used for industrial fabrication or processing of goods.
Label: Industrial facility

Comment: A business whose primary function is the serving of food for consumption on the premises.
Label: Eating establishment

Comment: A business whose primary function is the serving of alcoholic beverages for consumption on the premises.
Label: Drinking establishment

Comment: A property where travelers can pay for lodging and meals and other services.
Label: Hotel

Comment: A feature where one or many different sports can be played.
Label: Sports facility

Comment: A feature that is deemed to be of particular interest to society.
Label: Cultural facility

Comment: A feature that is associated with the movement of passengers and goods.
Label: Transport facility

Comment: A facility which may house fire fighters, and contains the equipment and vehicles.
Label: Fire station

Comment: The local office of a police force in a particular area.
Label: Police station

Comment: A medical facility that provides second level care.
Label: Hospital

Comment: A medical facility for outpatient primary level healthcare.
Label: Clinic

Comment: A property where young people receive primary and secondary education.
Label: School

Comment: A site providing higher/university education.
Label: University

Comment: A transaction record describes a single previous transaction (i.e. sale) of a property.
Label: Transaction record

Comment: A relationship between a property and its latest transaction record.
Label: has latest transaction record

Comment: A relationship between a transaction record and the associated transaction data.
Label: Transaction date

Comment: A relationship between a transaction record and the associated transaction price.
Label: Price paid

Comment: An index denoting the (average) property price evolution within a specific area over time.
Label: Property price index

Comment: A relationship between a property price index and the area it refers to.
Label: representative for

Comment: A relationship between the property price index and its actual time series history.
Label: has time series

Comment: The average property price per square metre in a particular area.
Label: Average price per square metre

Comment: Pound sterling per square metre.
Label: Pound sterling per sqm

Comment: A relationship between the average price per square metre and the area it refers to.
Label: representative for
